{{for|the record album|Golden Vessyl of Sound}}
{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}

'''Vessyl''' is an intelligent [[drinking glass]] announced in June 2014 by Mark One, but never released. The cup was to have embedded sensors and the capability of linking to a [[smartphone]] to provide its user with nutritional and other data on the beverage in the cup.<ref>{{citation|title=This Cup Tracks Exactly What You’re Drinking With Molecular Analysis|author=Kyle Vanhemert|date=June 12, 2014|work=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]|url=https://www.wired.com/2014/06/this-cup-tracks-exactly-what-youre-drinking-with-molecular-analysis/}}</ref><ref>{{citation|journal=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|title=The Vessyl Cup Can Tell Exactly How Many Calories Are In Your Drink|author=Katy Steinmetz |date=August 4, 2014|url=http://time.com/3067338/the-vessyl-cup-can-tell-exactly-what-youre-drinking/}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title=Vessyl Cup Knows What You Drink|date=June 12, 2014|author=Don Clark|work=Digits blog|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/06/12/vessyl-cup-knows-what-you-drink/}}</ref> The designers hoped to help users make better decisions about their health and overall consumption. The cup was expected to recharge on a proprietary base station, included in the product packaging. Industrial designer [[Yves Béhar]] and his design firm [https://fuseproject.com/ Fuseproject] were involved in its creation.<ref>{{citation|title=Vessyl smart cup can tell Coke from Pepsi| author=Nick Statt |date=June 12, 2014 |publisher=[[CNET]]|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/vessyl-smart-cup-knows-the-difference-between-coke-and-pepsi/}}</ref>

Originally, the device was expected to ship in "Early 2015". However, in March 2015, the manufacturer announced that the shipping date would slip to "Q4 2017".<ref>{{citation|title=Vessyl Backer Update #5|work=Vessyl Blog|author=Justin Lee and the Mark One team|date=March 13, 2015 |url=https://www.myvessyl.com/blog/posts/35-vessyl-backer-update-5}}</ref> once it has reached a satisfactory level of performance. {{As of|2018}}, Mark One, the company behind Vessyl, is no longer operating.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mark One|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/mark-one#section-overview|website=Crunchbase|publisher=Crunchbase|accessdate=16 February 2018|language=en}}</ref>

== Pryme Vessyl ==
With the announcement of a production delay to ensure the quality of the original Vessyl, the designers introduced a secondary product, Pryme Vessyl, released to the public in November 2015 and available to early supporters by means of a free opt-in program<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://myvessyl.com/blog/vessyl-backer-update-9/|title=Vessyl Backer Update #9 {{!}} Vessyl|website=myvessyl.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref>, orders which were in many cases not fulfilled.

